gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Hawks 141, Warriors 134
gameRecap.excerpt: The Hawks comeback and win in overtime to defeat the Warriors, 141-134. Trae Young recorded 35 points (7-11 3PM) and six assists for the Hawks, with Onyeka Okongwu adding 22 points and a season-high 16 rebounds in the victory. Stephen Curry notched a season-high 60 points (10-23 3PM) along with 6 rebounds and four assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Hawks improve to 22-27, while the Warriors fall to 21-25.
